68        +  %local _qpath;

83        +

85        +    %put ERROR: Failed while including %superq(path). SYSERR=&syserr;

92        +%macro _sassyverse_include_list(root=, files=, out_failed=);
93        +  %local _n _i _file _path _ok;
94        +  %let &out_failed=0;
95        +
96        +  %let _n=%sysfunc(countw(%superq(files), |, m));
97        +  %do _i=1 %to &_n;
98        +    %let _file=%sysfunc(strip(%scan(%superq(files), &_i, |, m)));
99        +    %if %length(%superq(_file)) > 0 %then %do;
100       +      %let _path=%superq(root)%superq(_file);
101       +      %_sassyverse_include(path=%superq(_path), out_status=_ok);
102       +      %if &_ok = 0 %then %do;
103       +        %let &out_failed=1;
104       +        %return;
105       +      %end;
106       +    %end;

232       +%macro import_variable(varname);
233       +/* This is the main import code block. It runs when all the applicable conditions pass. */
234       +    %global &varname.;
235       +    %if "%qsubstr(%superq(base_path), %length(%superq(base_path)), 1)" = "/" %then
236       +        %let file=&base_path.&module..sas;
237       +    %else
238       +        %let file=&base_path/&module..sas;
239       +
240       +    %if %sysfunc(fileexist(&file.)) %then %do;
241       +        %include "&file.";
242       +
243       +        data _null_;
244       +            call execute( '%let ' || "&varname." || ' = 1' );
245       +        run;
246       +        %put NOTE: Module &module. imported successfully.;
247       +    %end;
248       +
249       +    %else %do;
250       +        %put ERROR: Module &module. not found at &file.;
251       +    %end;
252       +%mend import_variable;

254       +%macro sbmod(
255       +    module /* Module name to import */
256       +    , base_path= /* Folder containing the module to import */
257       +    , reload=NO /* If the module has already been defined in this session, should it be redefined? Generally no, but
257      !+during macro development this could make sense. */);
258       +	/*
259       +		The `sbmod` macro is used to import a module into the global scope.			
260       +		The module is only imported once, and subsequent calls to `sbmod` with the	
261       +		same module name will not re-import the module. (This is the goal of the varname)
262       +		variable. The module is assumed to be located in the directory				
263       +		`/sas/data/project/EG/aweaver/macros/` and have the file extension `.sas`.	
264       +																					
265       +		Usage:																		
7                                                          The SAS System                            14:54 Monday, February 16, 2026

266       +		%sbmod(module_name);														
267       +		Includes the module `module_name` into the global scope, assuming you are	
268       +		using Andy's macro repository.												
269       +																					
270       +		%sbmod(module_name, base_path=/path/to/modules);							
271       +		Includes the module `module_name` into the global scope, where the module	
272       +		is located at `/path/to/modules/module_name.sas`.							
273       +	*/
274       +    %let varname=_imported__&module.;
275       +	%if %length(&varname.) >= 32 %then
276       +		%let varname=%truncate_varname(&varname.);
277       +    %if %length(%superq(base_path))=0 %then %do;
278       +        %if %symexist(_sassyverse_base_path) %then %let base_path=%superq(_sassyverse_base_path);
279       +        %else %let base_path=/sas/data/project/EG/aweaver/macros;
280       +    %end;
281       +
282       +    %if %symexist(&varname.) ne 1 %then %do;
283       +        %import_variable(&varname.);
284       +    %end;
285       +    %else %do;
286       +        %if (%symexist(&varname.)=1)
287       +            and ("&reload." ne "NO") %then %do;
288       +            %import_variable(&varname.);
289       +        %end;
290       +        %else %do;
291       +            %put NOTE: Module &module. already imported.;
292       +        %end;
293       +    %end;
294       +%mend sbmod;
NOTE: The macro SBMOD completed compilation without errors.
      67 instructions 1712 bytes.

416       +%macro assertTrue(condition, message);
417       +	/*
418       +	Assert that the given condition that evaluates to either 0
419       +	(for false) or 1 (for true) is true.
420       +
421       +	Logs a PASS if 1, FAIL if 0, and ERROR if anything else.
422       +
423       +	@param condition : Macro expression resolving to 1 for true
424       +	or 0 for false
425       +	@param message : A message that prints regardless of whether the
426       +	test passes to identify and describe the test.
427       +	 */
428       +	%itit_globals;
429       +	%if %symbol_dne(isCurrentlyInTestCase) %then %let isCurrentlyInTestCase=0;
430       +	%let result=0;
431       +
432       +	%let testPass=%eval(&testCount - &testFailures);
433       +	%let testCount=%eval(&testCount + 1);
434       +
435       +	%if %eval(&condition)=1 %then %do;
436       +		%let result=1;
437       +		%let testPass=%eval(&testPass + 1);
438       +		%put &logPASS. - &testPass.|&testFailures.|&testErrors. - &message;
439       +	%end;
440       +	%else %if %eval(&condition)=0 %then %do;
441       +		%let testFailures=%eval(&testFailures + 1);
442       +		%put &logFAIL. - &testPass.|&testFailures.|&testErrors. - &message;
443       +	%end;
444       +	%else %do;
445       +		%let result=-1;
446       +		%let testErrors=%eval(&testErrors + 1);
447       +		%put &logERROR. - &testPass.|&testFailures.|&testErrors. - &message.;
448       +		%put &logERROR. - &testPass.|&testFailures.|&testErrors. - &condition.
449       +			evaluates to %eval(&condition);
12                                                         The SAS System                            14:54 Monday, February 16, 2026

450       +		%put &logERROR. - &testPass.|&testFailures.|&testErrors. - &condition.
451       +			must evaluate to either 0 or 1;
452       +	%end;
453       +
454       +	%if &isCurrentlyInTestCase.=1 %then %do;
455       +		%let testCaseCount=%eval(&testCaseCount + 1);
456       +		%if %eval(&result=0) %then %let testCaseFailures=%eval(&testCaseFailures + 1);

1449      +    For example, if parmbuf is "a,b,c", sep is ",", and out_prefix is "param", this
1450      +    macro will create macro variables &param1=a, &param2=b, and &param3=c,
1451      +    plus &param_n=3.
1452      +
1453      +    Since "," is the separator by default, if a comma is needed as a literal in the
1454      +    parameters, the caller should wrap the comma in {}, eg
1455      +
1456      +    %parmbuf_parser(a{,}c)
1457      +     will create &param1=a,c -- not 2 parameters but 1 parameter with a literal comma separating a and c.
1458      +*/
1459      +%macro parmbuf_parser(parmbuf, sep=%str(,), out_prefix=param);
1460      +    %local buf sep_q seplen len i ch maybe_sep close curr count esc;
1461      +
1462      +    %let buf=%superq(parmbuf);
1463      +    %let sep_q=%superq(sep);
1464      +    %if %length(&sep_q)=0 %then %let sep_q=%str(,);
1465      +    %let seplen=%length(&sep_q);
1466      +
1467      +    %global &out_prefix._n;
1468      +    %if %length(%superq(buf))=0 %then %do;
1469      +        %let &out_prefix._n=0;
1470      +        %return;
1471      +    %end;
1472      +
1473      +    %let len=%length(&buf);
1474      +    %let count=1;
1475      +    %let curr=;
1476      +    %let i=1;
1477      +
1478      +    %do %while(&i <= &len);
1479      +        %let ch=%qsubstr(&buf, &i, 1);
1480      +
1481      +        %if %superq(ch)=%str({) %then %do;
1482      +            %let esc=0;
1483      +            %if &seplen > 0 %then %do;
1484      +                %if %eval(&i + &seplen + 1) <= &len %then %do;
1485      +                    %let maybe_sep=%qsubstr(&buf, %eval(&i+1), &seplen);
1486      +                    %let close=%qsubstr(&buf, %eval(&i+1+&seplen), 1);
1487      +                    %if %superq(maybe_sep)=%superq(sep_q) and %superq(close)=%str(}) %then %do;
1488      +                        %let curr=%superq(curr)%superq(sep_q);
1489      +                        %let i=%eval(&i + &seplen + 2);
1490      +                        %let esc=1;
1491      +                    %end;
1492      +                %end;
1493      +            %end;
1494      +
1495      +            %if &esc=0 %then %do;
1496      +                %let curr=%superq(curr)%superq(ch);
33                                                         The SAS System                            14:54 Monday, February 16, 2026

1497      +                %let i=%eval(&i+1);
1498      +            %end;
1499      +        %end;
1500      +        %else %if &seplen > 0 %then %do;
1501      +            %let maybe_sep=%qsubstr(&buf, &i, &seplen);
1502      +            %if %superq(maybe_sep)=%superq(sep_q) %then %do;
1503      +                %global &out_prefix.&count;
1504      +                %let &out_prefix.&count=%superq(curr);
1505      +                %let count=%eval(&count+1);
1506      +                %let curr=;
1507      +                %let i=%eval(&i + &seplen);
1508      +            %end;
1509      +            %else %do;
1510      +                %let curr=%superq(curr)%superq(ch);
1511      +                %let i=%eval(&i+1);
1512      +            %end;
1513      +        %end;
1514      +        %else %do;
1515      +            %let curr=%superq(curr)%superq(ch);
1516      +            %let i=%eval(&i+1);
1517      +        %end;
1518      +    %end;
1519      +
1520      +    %global &out_prefix.&count;
1521      +    %let &out_prefix.&count=%superq(curr);
1522      +    %let &out_prefix._n=&count;
1523      +%mend;
NOTE: The macro PARMBUF_PARSER completed compilation without errors.
      205 instructions 4680 bytes.

1985      +%macro roundto(
1986      +    x /* Value to round */
1987      +    , n_digits /* Number of digits to round to. Defaults to 0. */
1988      +);
1989      +    %if %length(%superq(n_digits))=0
1990      +        %then %let n_digits=0;
1991      +
1992      +    %let n=%eval(10 ** &n_digits.);
1993      +    %let prod=%sysevalf(&n. * &x.);
1994      +    %let out=%sysfunc(round(&prod.));
1995      +    %let out=%sysevalf(&out. / &n.);
1996      +    &out.
1997      +%mend roundto;

2910      +/* Split a parenthesized macro parmbuff string into top-level comma segments. */
2911      +%macro _pipr_split_parmbuff_segments(buf=, out_n=, out_prefix=seg);
2912      +  %global &out_n;
2913      +
2914      +  data _null_;
68                                                         The SAS System                            14:54 Monday, February 16, 2026

2915      +    length buf seg $32767 ch quote $1;
2916      +    buf = symget('buf');
2917      +
2918      +    if length(buf) >= 2 and substr(buf, 1, 1) = '(' and substr(buf, length(buf), 1) = ')' then
2919      +      buf = substr(buf, 2, length(buf) - 2);
2920      +
2921      +    depth = 0;
2922      +    seg = '';
2923      +    quote = '';
2924      +   __seg_count = 0;
2925      +
2926      +    do i = 1 to length(buf);
2927      +      ch = substr(buf, i, 1);
2928      +
2929      +      if quote = '' then do;
2930      +        if ch = "'" or ch = '"' then quote = ch;
2931      +        else if ch = '(' then depth + 1;
2932      +        else if ch = ')' and depth > 0 then depth + (-1);
2933      +      end;
2934      +      else if ch = quote then quote = '';
2935      +
2936      +      if quote = '' and depth = 0 and ch = ',' then do;
2937      +       __seg_count + 1;
2938      +        call symputx(cats(symget('out_prefix'),__seg_count), strip(seg), 'G');
2939      +        seg = '';
2940      +      end;
2941      +      else seg = cats(seg, ch);
2942      +    end;
2943      +
2944      +    if length(strip(seg)) then do;
2945      +     __seg_count + 1;
2946      +      call symputx(cats(symget('out_prefix'),__seg_count), strip(seg), 'G');
2947      +    end;
2948      +
2949      +    call symputx(symget('out_n'),__seg_count, 'G');
2950      +  run;
2951      +%mend;
NOTE: The macro _PIPR_SPLIT_PARMBUFF_SEGMENTS completed compilation without errors.
      22 instructions 1448 bytes.

2953      +/* Returns 1 when unit tests are enabled for this session, else 0. */
2954      +%macro _pipr_in_unit_tests;

2956      +    %if %superq(__unit_tests)=1 %then 1;

4790      +%macro _sel_cols_where_predicate(predicate=, out_predicate=);
4791      +  %local _raw _out;
4792      +  %if not %sysmacexist(_sel_lambda_normalize) %then %_abort(cols_where() requires selector lambda helpers to be loaded.);
4793      +  %_sel_lambda_normalize(expr=%superq(predicate), out_expr=_raw);
4794      +  %_sel_require_nonempty(value=%superq(_raw), msg=cols_where() requires a non-empty predicate expression.);
4795      +

4801      +    raw = prxchange('s/\.type\b/type/i', -1, raw);
4802      +    raw = prxchange('s/\.length\b/length/i', -1, raw);
4803      +    raw = prxchange('s/\.label\b/label/i', -1, raw);

4839      +%macro _sel_tokenize(expr=, out_n=, out_prefix=_sel_tok);
4840      +  %global &out_n;
4841      +
4842      +  data _null_;
4843      +    length expr tok $32767 ch quote $1;
4844      +    expr = symget('expr');
4845      +    tok = '';
4846      +    quote = '';
4847      +    depth = 0;
4848      +    n = 0;
4849      +
4850      +    do i = 1 to length(expr);
4851      +      ch = substr(expr, i, 1);
4852      +
4853      +      if quote = '' then do;
4854      +        if ch = "'" or ch = '"' then quote = ch;
4855      +        else if ch = '(' then depth + 1;
4856      +        else if ch = ')' and depth > 0 then depth + (-1);
4857      +      end;
4858      +      else if ch = quote then quote = '';
4859      +
4860      +      if quote = '' and depth = 0 and (ch = ',' or ch in (' ', '09'x, '0A'x, '0D'x)) then do;
4861      +        if length(strip(tok)) then do;
4862      +          n + 1;
4863      +          call symputx(cats(symget('out_prefix'), n), strip(tok), 'L');
4864      +          tok = '';
4865      +        end;
4866      +      end;
4867      +      else tok = cats(tok, ch);
4868      +    end;
4869      +
4870      +    if length(strip(tok)) then do;
4871      +      n + 1;
4872      +      call symputx(cats(symget('out_prefix'), n), strip(tok), 'L');
4873      +    end;
4874      +
4875      +    call symputx(symget('out_n'), n, 'L');
307                                                        The SAS System                            14:54 Monday, February 16, 2026

4876      +  run;
4877      +%mend;
NOTE: The macro _SEL_TOKENIZE completed compilation without errors.

5288      +%macro _selector_matches(ds=, regex=, out_cols=);
5289      +  %local _regex _prx _re_ok;
5290      +  %global _sel_matches_re;
5291      +
5292      +  %let _regex=%superq(regex);
5293      +  %_sel_require_nonempty(value=%superq(_regex), msg=matches() requires a non-empty regex pattern.);
5294      +  %_sel_regex_to_prx(regex=%superq(_regex), out_prx=_prx, default_flags=i);
5295      +  %_sel_require_nonempty(value=%superq(_prx), msg=matches() could not parse regex pattern.);
5296      +
5297      +  %let _sel_matches_re=%superq(_prx);
5298      +  %let _re_ok=1;
5299      +  data _null_;
5300      +    _sel_re = prxparse(symget('_sel_matches_re'));
5301      +    if missing(_sel_re) then call symputx('_re_ok', 0, 'L');
5302      +    else call prxfree(_sel_re);
5303      +  run;
5304      +  %if &_re_ok = 0 %then %_abort(matches() received an invalid regex pattern: %superq(_regex));
5305      +
5306      +  %_sel_collect_by_predicate(
5307      +    ds=&ds,
5308      +    predicate=%str(prxmatch(symget('_sel_matches_re'), strip(name)) > 0),
5309      +    out_cols=&out_cols,
5310      +    empty_msg=matches('%superq(_regex)') matched no columns in &ds.
5311      +  );
5312      +%mend;

5508      +/* step expansion with:
5509      +   - automatic quoting for positional argument: %bquote(&args)
5510      +   - injection of data/out/validate
5511      +   - injection of as_view= (planned per step)
5512      +*/
5513      +%macro _apply_step(step, in, out, pipe_validate, as_view);
5514      +  %local is_pos;
5515      +
5516      +  %_step_parse(%superq(step), _pipe_step_verb, _pipe_step_args);
5517      +  %let is_pos=%_is_positional_verb(&_pipe_step_verb);
5518      +  %_step_has_validate(&_pipe_step_args, _pipe_has_validate);
5519      +
5520      +  %if &is_pos %then %do;
5521      +    /* Positional verbs: first arg auto-quoted to protect commas */
5522      +    %_step_call_positional(&_pipe_step_verb, &_pipe_step_args, &in, &out, &as_view, &pipe_validate, &_pipe_has_validate);
5523      +  %end;
5524      +  %else %do;
5525      +    /* Named-args verbs: args come after injected params */
5526      +    %_step_call_named(&_pipe_step_verb, &_pipe_step_args, &in, &out, &as_view, &pipe_validate, &_pipe_has_validate);
5527      +  %end;
5528      +%mend;

5795      +%macro _filter_parse_parmbuff(
5796      +  where_in=,
5797      +  data_in=,
5798      +  out_in=,
5799      +  validate_in=,
5800      +  as_view_in=,
5801      +  out_where=,
5802      +  out_data=,
5803      +  out_out=,
5804      +  out_validate=,
5805      +  out_as_view=
5806      +);
5807      +  %local _buf _n _i _seg _head _eq _val _where_acc;
5808      +
5809      +  %let &out_where=%superq(where_in);
5810      +  %let &out_data=%superq(data_in);
5811      +  %let &out_out=%superq(out_in);
5812      +  %let &out_validate=%superq(validate_in);
5813      +  %let &out_as_view=%superq(as_view_in);
5814      +
5815      +  %let _where_acc=;
5816      +  %let _buf=%superq(syspbuff);
5817      +  %if %length(%superq(_buf)) > 2 %then %do;
5818      +    %if not %sysmacexist(_pipr_split_parmbuff_segments) %then
5819      +      %_abort(filter() requires pipr util helpers to be loaded.);

6163      +    - inner_join()       : user-facing, default method=HASH
6164      +    - left_join_hash()   : explicit hash left join
6165      +    - inner_join_hash()  : explicit hash inner join
6166      +    - left_join_sql()    : explicit SQL left join (PROC SQL)
6167      +    - inner_join_sql()   : explicit SQL inner join (PROC SQL)
6168      +
6169      +  Intended join shape:
6170      +    - many-to-1 lookup joins (right is unique on keys) are the primary target.
6171      +    - many-to-many joins (right duplicates on keys) are allowed only if you
6172      +      disable require_unique=, but semantics may be surprising (hash uses an
6173      +      arbitrary match; SQL multiplies rows).
6174      +
6175      +  NOTE: This file depends on:
6176      +    - %_abort
6177      +    - %_assert_ds_exists

6187      +/* Abort if right_keep contains any join keys. Duplicate column names in output
6188      +   are a common source of brittle downstream failures. */
6189      +%macro _join_right_keep_key_overlap(on=, right_keep=, out_has_overlap=, out_key=);
6190      +  %local i n k has_overlap overlap_key;
6191      +  %global &out_has_overlap &out_key;
6192      +
6193      +  %let has_overlap=0;
6194      +  %let overlap_key=;
6195      +  %if %length(%superq(right_keep))=0 %then %do;
6196      +    %let &out_has_overlap=0;
6197      +    %let &out_key=;
6198      +    %return;
6199      +  %end;
6200      +
6201      +  %let n=%sysfunc(countw(%superq(on), %str( ), q));
6202      +  %do i=1 %to &n;
6203      +    %let k=%scan(%superq(on), &i, %str( ), q);
6204      +    %if %sysfunc(indexw(%upcase(%superq(right_keep)), %upcase(&k))) > 0 %then %do;
6205      +      %let has_overlap=1;
6206      +      %let overlap_key=%superq(k);
6207      +      %goto overlap_done;
6208      +    %end;
6209      +  %end;
6210      +
6211      +%overlap_done:
6212      +  %let &out_has_overlap=&has_overlap;
6213      +  %let &out_key=&overlap_key;
6214      +%mend;

6273      +%macro _join_hash_emit(join_type=LEFT, obj=h, right=, on=, data=, out=, right_keep=, as_view=0);
6274      +  %local jt _as_view;

6276      +  %let _as_view=%_pipr_bool(%superq(as_view), default=0);
6277      +
6278      +  %if &_as_view %then %do;
6279      +    data &out / view=&out;

6283      +  %end;
6284      +
6285      +    /* Compile-time PDV alignment */
340                                                        The SAS System                            14:54 Monday, February 16, 2026

6286      +    if 0 then set &right(keep=&on &right_keep);
6287      +
6288      +    if _n_ = 1 then do;
6289      +      %_join_hash_define(obj=&obj, right=&right, on=&on, right_keep=&right_keep);
6290      +    end;
6291      +
6292      +    do until(eof);
6293      +      set &data end=eof;
6294      +
6295      +      /* reset right vars each row for correct LEFT join behavior */
6296      +      %if %length(%superq(right_keep)) %then %do;
6297      +        %_join_call_missing(varlist=&right_keep);
6298      +      %end;

6303      +        /* left join: always output */
6304      +        output;
6305      +      %end;
6306      +      %else %if &jt = INNER %then %do;
6307      +        /* inner join: only output matches */

6431      +
6432      +/* Picks HASH vs SQL for lookup-style joins.
6433      +
6434      +   Heuristic intent:
6435      +     - Prefer HASH when right is a true table (not a view), unique on keys,
6436      +       and estimated hash footprint is small enough.
6437      +     - Prefer SQL when right is a view (hash rebuilt each execution),
6438      +       or when size estimates are unavailable, or footprint likely large.
6439      +
6440      +   Outputs:
6441      +     - sets &out_method to HASH or SQL
6442      +     - sets global PIPR_JOIN_LAST_METHOD for testability (optional)
6443      +
6444      +   Parameters:
6445      +     auto_max_obs:         max right NOBS to prefer HASH (default 5e6)
343                                                        The SAS System                            14:54 Monday, February 16, 2026

6446      +     auto_max_mem_mb:      max estimated hash memory in MB to prefer HASH (default 512)
6447      +     auto_overhead_factor: multiplier for hash overhead (default 2.5)
6448      +     auto_prefer_hash:     1 forces HASH when estimates unavailable (default 0)
6449      +*/
6450      +%macro _join_auto_pick_method(
6451      +  data=,
6452      +  right=,
6453      +  on=,
6454      +  right_keep=,
6455      +  require_unique=1,
6456      +  as_view=0,
6457      +  out_method=,
6458      +  auto_max_obs=5000000,
6459      +  auto_max_mem_mb=512,
6460      +  auto_overhead_factor=2.5,
6461      +  auto_prefer_hash=0
6462      +);
6463      +  %local is_view nobs row_bytes cols mem_est_bytes mem_cap_bytes _require_unique _auto_prefer_hash;
6464      +  %let _require_unique=%_pipr_bool(%superq(require_unique), default=1);
6465      +  %let _auto_prefer_hash=%_pipr_bool(%superq(auto_prefer_hash), default=0);
6466      +
6467      +  %if %length(&out_method)=0 %then %_abort(_join_auto_pick_method requires out_method=);
6468      +
6469      +  /* If the caller wants strict lookup semantics, uniqueness is already enforced in validation.
6470      +     If require_unique=0, AUTO should generally avoid HASH because semantics diverge:
6471      +       - HASH: first match wins
6472      +       - SQL: multiplies rows
6473      +     So default to SQL unless user explicitly asks for HASH. */
6474      +  %if &_require_unique = 0 %then %do;
6475      +    %let &out_method=SQL;
6476      +    %global PIPR_JOIN_LAST_METHOD;
6477      +    %let PIPR_JOIN_LAST_METHOD=SQL;
6478      +    %return;
6479      +  %end;
6480      +
6481      +  %let is_view=%_ds_is_view(&right);
6482      +
6483      +  /* If right is a view, hash will be rebuilt every time the stream executes (especially painful in view pipelines).
6484      +     Prefer SQL (and possibly create view) in that case. */
6485      +  %if &is_view %then %do;
6486      +    %let &out_method=SQL;
6487      +    %global PIPR_JOIN_LAST_METHOD;
6488      +    %let PIPR_JOIN_LAST_METHOD=SQL;
6489      +    %return;
6490      +  %end;
6491      +
6492      +  /* Try to get right NOBS cheaply */
6493      +  %_ds_nobs_vtable(&right, nobs);
6494      +
6495      +  /* If NOBS unknown and auto_prefer_hash=0, choose SQL conservatively. */
6496      +  %if %length(&nobs)=0 %then %do;
6497      +    %if &_auto_prefer_hash %then %do;
6498      +      %let &out_method=HASH;
6499      +    %end;
6500      +    %else %do;
6501      +      %let &out_method=SQL;
6502      +    %end;
6503      +    %global PIPR_JOIN_LAST_METHOD;
344                                                        The SAS System                            14:54 Monday, February 16, 2026

6504      +    %let PIPR_JOIN_LAST_METHOD=&&&out_method;
6505      +    %return;
6506      +  %end;
6507      +
6508      +  /* Quick NOBS gate */
6509      +  %if %sysevalf(&nobs > &auto_max_obs) %then %do;
6510      +    %let &out_method=SQL;
6511      +    %global PIPR_JOIN_LAST_METHOD;
6512      +    %let PIPR_JOIN_LAST_METHOD=SQL;
6513      +    %return;
6514      +  %end;
6515      +
6516      +  /* Estimate memory footprint: nobs * row_bytes * overhead_factor */
6517      +  %let cols=&on &right_keep;
6518      +  %_ds_est_row_bytes(&right, &cols, row_bytes);
6519      +
6520      +  %if %length(&row_bytes)=0 %then %do;
6521      +    /* no estimate => conservative */
6522      +    %if &_auto_prefer_hash %then %let &out_method=HASH;
6523      +    %else %let &out_method=SQL;
6524      +
6525      +    %global PIPR_JOIN_LAST_METHOD;
6526      +    %let PIPR_JOIN_LAST_METHOD=&&&out_method;
6527      +    %return;
6528      +  %end;
6529      +
6530      +  %let mem_est_bytes=%sysevalf(&nobs * &row_bytes * &auto_overhead_factor);
6531      +  %let mem_cap_bytes=%sysevalf(&auto_max_mem_mb * 1024 * 1024);
6532      +
6533      +  %if %sysevalf(&mem_est_bytes <= &mem_cap_bytes) %then %let &out_method=HASH;
6534      +  %else %let &out_method=SQL;
6535      +
6536      +  %global PIPR_JOIN_LAST_METHOD;
6537      +  %let PIPR_JOIN_LAST_METHOD=&&&out_method;
6538      +%mend;
NOTE: The macro _JOIN_AUTO_PICK_METHOD completed compilation without errors.

6728      +/*==============================================================================
6729      +  User-facing verbs: left_join / inner_join (dispatcher)
6730      +==============================================================================*/
6731      +
6732      +%macro left_join(
6733      +  right,
6734      +  on=,
6735      +  data=,
6736      +  out=,
6737      +  right_keep=,
6738      +  method=HASH,
6739      +  validate=1,
6740      +  require_unique=1,
6741      +  strict_char_len=0,
6742      +  as_view=0,
6743      +  /* AUTO tuning knobs (optional) */
6744      +  auto_max_obs=5000000,
6745      +  auto_max_mem_mb=512,
6746      +  auto_overhead_factor=2.5,
6747      +  auto_prefer_hash=0,
6748      +  error_msg=left_join() failed due to invalid input parameters
6749      +);
6750      +  %local m picked _require_unique _as_view;
6751      +  %let _require_unique=%_pipr_bool(%superq(require_unique), default=1);
6752      +  %let _as_view=%_pipr_bool(%superq(as_view), default=0);
6753      +
6754      +  %let m=%upcase(&method);
6755      +
6756      +  %if "%superq(m)" = "AUTO" %then %do;
6757      +    %let picked=;
6758      +    %_join_auto_pick_method(
6759      +      data=&data,
6760      +      right=&right,
6761      +      on=&on,
6762      +      right_keep=&right_keep,
6763      +      require_unique=&_require_unique,
6764      +      as_view=&_as_view,
6765      +      out_method=picked,
6766      +      auto_max_obs=&auto_max_obs,
6767      +      auto_max_mem_mb=&auto_max_mem_mb,
6768      +      auto_overhead_factor=&auto_overhead_factor,
6769      +      auto_prefer_hash=&auto_prefer_hash
6770      +    );
6771      +    %let m=%upcase(&picked);
6772      +  %end;
6773      +
6774      +  %if "%superq(m)" = "HASH" %then %do;
6775      +    %left_join_hash(&right, on=&on, data=&data, out=&out, right_keep=&right_keep,
6776      +      validate=&validate, require_unique=&_require_unique, strict_char_len=&strict_char_len, as_view=&_as_view,
6776     !+error_msg=&error_msg);
6777      +  %end;
6778      +  %else %if "%superq(m)" = "SQL" %then %do;
6779      +    %left_join_sql(&right, on=&on, data=&data, out=&out, right_keep=&right_keep,
6780      +      validate=&validate, require_unique=&_require_unique, strict_char_len=&strict_char_len, as_view=&_as_view,
349                                                        The SAS System                            14:54 Monday, February 16, 2026

6780     !+error_msg=&error_msg);
6781      +  %end;
6782      +  %else %do;
6783      +    %_abort(left_join(): unknown method=&method (expected HASH, SQL, or AUTO));
6784      +  %end;
6785      +%mend;

6847      +%macro test_join();
6848      +  %_pipr_require_assert;
6849      +  %test_suite(join);
6850      +
6851      +  /*-----------------------
6852      +    Base fixtures
6853      +  -----------------------*/
6854      +  data work._j_left;
6855      +    input id x;
6856      +    datalines;
6857      +1 10
6858      +2 20
6859      +2 21
6860      +3 30
6861      +;
6862      +  run;
6863      +
6864      +  data work._j_right;
6865      +    input id r1;
6866      +    datalines;
6867      +1 100
6868      +3 300
6869      +;
6870      +  run;
6871      +
6872      +  /*-----------------------
6873      +    Hash LEFT: preserves rowcount + missing for non-matches
6874      +  -----------------------*/
6875      +  %test_case(left_join_hash preserves left rowcount and missing);
6876      +    %left_join_hash(work._j_right, on=id, data=work._j_left, out=work._j_lh, right_keep=r1, require_unique=1);
6877      +
6878      +    proc sql noprint;
6879      +      select count(*) into :_n_lh trimmed from work._j_lh;
6880      +      select sum(missing(r1)) into :_miss_lh trimmed from work._j_lh where id=2;
6881      +      select sum(r1) into :_sum_lh trimmed from work._j_lh;
6882      +    quit;
6883      +
6884      +    %assertEqual(&_n_lh., 4);
6885      +    %assertEqual(&_miss_lh., 2);
6886      +    /* sum should be 100 + 300 = 400; missing contributes 0 */
6887      +    %assertEqual(&_sum_lh., 400);
6888      +  %test_summary;
6889      +
351                                                        The SAS System                            14:54 Monday, February 16, 2026

6890      +  /*-----------------------
6891      +    Hash INNER: drops non-matches
6892      +  -----------------------*/
6893      +  %test_case(inner_join_hash drops non-matches);
6894      +    %inner_join_hash(work._j_right, on=id, data=work._j_left, out=work._j_ih, right_keep=r1, require_unique=1);
6895      +
6896      +    proc sql noprint;
6897      +      select count(*) into :_n_ih trimmed from work._j_ih;
6898      +      select sum(r1) into :_sum_ih trimmed from work._j_ih;
6899      +    quit;
6900      +

6902      +    %assertEqual(&_sum_ih., 400);
6903      +  %test_summary;
6904      +

6910      +
6911      +    proc sql noprint;
6912      +      select count(*) into :_n_ls trimmed from work._j_ls;
6913      +      select sum(case when r1 is null then 1 else 0 end) into :_miss_ls trimmed from work._j_ls where id=2;
6914      +      select sum(r1) into :_sum_ls trimmed from work._j_ls;
6915      +    quit;
6916      +
6917      +    %assertEqual(&_n_ls., 4);
6918      +    %assertEqual(&_miss_ls., 2);
6919      +    %assertEqual(&_sum_ls., 400);

6927      +

6931      +    quit;

6933      +    %assertEqual(&_n_is., 2);

7248      +  stmt_in=,

7256      +  out_validate=,

7258      +);
7259      +  %local _buf _n _i _seg _head _eq _val _stmt_acc;
7260      +
7261      +  %let &out_stmt=%superq(stmt_in);
7262      +  %let &out_data=%superq(data_in);
7263      +  %let &out_out=%superq(out_in);
7264      +  %let &out_validate=%superq(validate_in);
7265      +  %let &out_as_view=%superq(as_view_in);

7271      +    %_pipr_split_parmbuff_segments(buf=%superq(_buf), out_n=_n, out_prefix=_mt_seg);
7272      +

7277      +        %if %sysfunc(indexw(DATA OUT VALIDATE AS_VIEW STMT, &_head)) > 0 %then %do;

7285      +          %else %if &_head=AS_VIEW %then %let &out_as_view=%sysfunc(strip(%superq(_val)));

7301      +%macro _mutate_normalize_stmt(stmt, out_stmt);
7302      +  %local _raw _norm;
7303      +  %global &out_stmt;
360                                                        The SAS System                            14:54 Monday, February 16, 2026

7304      +  %let _raw=%sysfunc(strip(%unquote(%superq(stmt))));
7305      +  %if %length(%superq(_raw))=0 %then %_abort(mutate() requires a non-empty expression or statement block.);
7306      +
7307      +  data _null_;
7308      +    length raw norm tok $32767 ch quote $1;
7309      +    raw = strip(symget('_raw'));
7310      +
7311      +    if index(raw, ';') > 0 then norm = raw;
7312      +    else do;
7313      +      norm = '';
7314      +      tok = '';
7315      +      quote = '';
7316      +      depth = 0;
7317      +
7318      +      do i = 1 to length(raw);
7319      +        ch = substr(raw, i, 1);
7320      +
7321      +        if quote = '' then do;
7322      +          if ch = "'" or ch = '"' then quote = ch;
7323      +          else if ch = '(' then depth + 1;
7324      +          else if ch = ')' and depth > 0 then depth + (-1);
7325      +        end;
7326      +        else if ch = quote then quote = '';
7327      +
7328      +        if quote = '' and depth = 0 and ch = ',' then do;
7329      +          if length(strip(tok)) then norm = catx(' ', norm, cats(strip(tok), ';'));
7330      +          tok = '';
7331      +        end;
7332      +        else tok = cats(tok, ch);
7333      +      end;
7334      +
7335      +      if length(strip(tok)) then norm = catx(' ', norm, cats(strip(tok), ';'));
7336      +    end;
7337      +
7338      +    norm = strip(norm);
7339      +    if length(norm) > 0 and substr(norm, length(norm), 1) ne ';' then norm = cats(norm, ';');
7340      +    call symputx('_norm', norm, 'L');
7341      +  run;

7656      +%macro _rename_parse_pairs(rename_pairs, out_old, out_map);
7657      +  %local i pair old_var new_var num_pairs old_list map;
7658      +  %global &out_old &out_map;
7659      +
7660      +  %let old_list=;
7661      +  %let map=;
7662      +  %let num_pairs=%sysfunc(countw(%superq(rename_pairs), %str( ), q));
7663      +  %if &num_pairs = 0 %then %_abort(rename() requires rename_pairs=);
7664      +
7665      +  %do i=1 %to &num_pairs.;
7666      +    %let pair=%scan(%superq(rename_pairs), &i., %str( ), q);
7667      +    %let old_var=%scan(%superq(pair), 1, =, q);
7668      +    %let new_var=%scan(%superq(pair), 2, =, q);
368                                                        The SAS System                            14:54 Monday, February 16, 2026

7669      +
7670      +    %if %length(%superq(old_var))=0 or %length(%superq(new_var))=0 %then %do;
7671      +      %_abort(rename() requires pairs in old=new form. Bad token: %superq(pair).);
7672      +    %end;
7673      +
7674      +    %let old_list=&old_list %superq(old_var);
7675      +    %let map=&map %superq(old_var)=%superq(new_var);
7676      +  %end;
7677      +
7678      +  %let old_list=%sysfunc(compbl(&old_list));
7679      +  %let map=%sysfunc(compbl(&map));
7680      +  %let &out_old=&old_list;
7681      +  %let &out_map=&map;
7682      +%mend;

8089      +  steps_in=,
8090      +  data_in=,

8092      +  validate_in=,

8101      +  out_use_views=,

8103      +  out_debug=,

8105      +);
8106      +  %local buf i seg seg_head seg_val eq_pos;
8107      +  %global __seg_count;
8108      +
8109      +  %let &out_steps=%superq(steps_in);
8110      +  %let &out_data=%superq(data_in);
8111      +  %let &out_out=%superq(out_in);

8114      +  %let &out_view_output=%superq(view_output_in);
8115      +  %let &out_debug=%superq(debug_in);
8116      +  %let &out_cleanup=%superq(cleanup_in);
8117      +
8118      +  %let buf=%superq(syspbuff);
8119      +  %if %length(%superq(buf)) > 2 %then %do;
8120      +    %_pipe_split_parmbuff_segments(buf=%superq(buf), out_n=__seg_count, out_prefix=seg);
8121      +
8122      +    %do i=1 %to &__seg_count;
8123      +      %let seg=%superq(seg&i);
8124      +      %let seg_head=%upcase(%sysfunc(strip(%scan(%superq(seg), 1, =))));
8125      +
8126      +      %if %sysfunc(indexw(DATA OUT VALIDATE USE_VIEWS VIEW_OUTPUT DEBUG CLEANUP STEPS, &seg_head)) > 0 %then %do;
8127      +        %let eq_pos=%index(%superq(seg), %str(=));
8128      +        %if &eq_pos > 0 %then %let seg_val=%substr(%superq(seg), %eval(&eq_pos+1));

8132      +        %else %if &seg_head=OUT %then %let &out_out=%sysfunc(strip(%superq(seg_val)));
8133      +        %else %if &seg_head=VALIDATE %then %let &out_validate=%sysfunc(strip(%superq(seg_val)));

8135      +        %else %if &seg_head=VIEW_OUTPUT %then %let &out_view_output=%sysfunc(strip(%superq(seg_val)));
8136      +        %else %if &seg_head=DEBUG %then %let &out_debug=%sysfunc(strip(%superq(seg_val)));
8137      +        %else %if &seg_head=CLEANUP %then %let &out_cleanup=%sysfunc(strip(%superq(seg_val)));
8138      +        %else %if &seg_head=STEPS %then %let &out_steps=%sysfunc(strip(%superq(seg_val)));
8139      +      %end;
8140      +      %else %if %length(%superq(&out_steps))=0 %then %let &out_steps=%sysfunc(strip(%superq(seg)));

8142      +  %end;

8341      +    out=&out,
8342      +    tmp1=&tmp1,
8343      +    tmp2=&tmp2,
8344      +    use_views=&use_views,
8345      +    view_output=&view_output,
8346      +    supports_view=&supports_view,
8347      +    out_as_view=as_view,
8348      +    out_next=_nxt
8349      +  );
8350      +
8351      +  %if &debug %then %do;
8352      +    %put NOTE: PIPE step &i/&n: %superq(step);
8353      +    %put NOTE:   verb=&verb supports_view=&supports_view planned_as_view=&as_view;
8354      +    %put NOTE:   in=&cur;
8355      +    %put NOTE:   out=&_nxt;
8356      +  %end;
8357      +
8358      +  %_apply_step(%superq(step), &cur, &_nxt, &validate, &as_view);
8359      +  %_assert_ds_exists(&_nxt, error_msg=Step &i did not create expected output. Step token: %superq(step));
8360      +
8361      +  %let &out_next=&_nxt;
8362      +%mend;
8363      +
8364      +%macro _pipe_cleanup_temps(tmp1=, tmp2=, out=, cleanup=1);
8365      +  %if &cleanup %then %do;
8366      +    %if %upcase(&tmp1) ne %upcase(&out) %then %do;
8367      +      proc datasets lib=work nolist; delete %scan(&tmp1, 2, .); quit;
8368      +    %end;
8369      +    %if %upcase(&tmp2) ne %upcase(&out) %then %do;
8370      +      proc datasets lib=work nolist; delete %scan(&tmp2, 2, .); quit;
8371      +    %end;
8372      +  %end;
8373      +%mend;
8374      +
8375      +%macro _pipe_execute(
8376      +  steps=,
8377      +  data=,
8378      +  out=,
8379      +  validate=1,
8380      +  use_views=1,
8381      +  view_output=0,
8382      +  debug=0,
8383      +  cleanup=1
8384      +);
8385      +  %local i n cur nxt tmp1 tmp2 step;
8386      +
8387      +  %let tmp1=%_tmpds(prefix=_p1_);
8388      +  %let tmp2=%_tmpds(prefix=_p2_);
8389      +  %let cur=&data;
8390      +
383                                                        The SAS System                            14:54 Monday, February 16, 2026

8391      +  %_pipe_steps_count(steps=%superq(steps), out_n=n);
8392      +  %if &n = 0 %then %_abort(pipe() requires steps= delimited by '|'.);
8393      +
8394      +  %do i=1 %to &n;
8395      +    %_pipe_get_step(steps=%superq(steps), index=&i, out_step=step);
8396      +    %_pipe_execute_step(
8397      +      step=%superq(step),
8398      +      i=&i,
8399      +      n=&n,
8400      +      cur=&cur,
8401      +      out=&out,
8402      +      tmp1=&tmp1,
8403      +      tmp2=&tmp2,
8404      +      use_views=&use_views,
8405      +      view_output=&view_output,
8406      +      debug=&debug,
8407      +      validate=&validate,
8408      +      out_next=nxt
8409      +    );
8410      +    %let cur=&nxt;
8411      +  %end;
8412      +
8413      +  %_pipe_cleanup_temps(tmp1=&tmp1, tmp2=&tmp2, out=&out, cleanup=&cleanup);
8414      +%mend;
8415      +
8416      +%macro pipe(
8417      +  steps=,
8418      +  data=,
8419      +  out=,
8420      +  validate=1,
8421      +  use_views=1,
8422      +  view_output=0,
8423      +  debug=0,
8424      +  cleanup=1
8425      +) / parmbuff;
8426      +  %local steps_work data_work out_work validate_work use_views_work view_output_work debug_work cleanup_work;
8427      +  %local collect_out;
8428      +
8429      +  %_pipe_parse_parmbuff(
8430      +    steps_in=%superq(steps),
8431      +    data_in=%superq(data),
8432      +    out_in=%superq(out),
8433      +    validate_in=%superq(validate),
8434      +    use_views_in=%superq(use_views),
8435      +    view_output_in=%superq(view_output),
8436      +    debug_in=%superq(debug),
8437      +    cleanup_in=%superq(cleanup),
8438      +    out_steps=steps_work,
8439      +    out_data=data_work,
8440      +    out_out=out_work,
8441      +    out_validate=validate_work,
8442      +    out_use_views=use_views_work,
8443      +    out_view_output=view_output_work,
8444      +    out_debug=debug_work,
8445      +    out_cleanup=cleanup_work
8446      +  );
8447      +
8448      +  %if %length(%superq(steps_work))=0 %then %_abort(pipe() requires steps delimited by '|'.);
384                                                        The SAS System                            14:54 Monday, February 16, 2026

8449      +
8450      +  %_pipe_infer_data(
8451      +    steps_in=%superq(steps_work),
8452      +    data_in=%superq(data_work),
8453      +    out_steps=steps_work,
8454      +    out_data=data_work
8455      +  );
8456      +
8457      +  %_pipe_extract_collect_out(
8458      +    steps_in=%superq(steps_work),
8459      +    out_in=%superq(out_work),
8460      +    out_steps=steps_work,
8461      +    out_out=out_work,
8462      +    out_collect_out=collect_out
8463      +  );
8464      +
8465      +  %_pipe_clean_value(value=%superq(data_work), out=data_work);
8466      +  %_pipe_clean_value(value=%superq(out_work), out=out_work);
8467      +  %_pipe_clean_value(value=%superq(steps_work), out=steps_work);
8468      +
8469      +  %let validate_work=%_pipr_bool(%superq(validate_work), default=1);
8470      +  %let use_views_work=%_pipr_bool(%superq(use_views_work), default=1);
8471      +  %let view_output_work=%_pipr_bool(%superq(view_output_work), default=0);
8472      +  %let debug_work=%_pipr_bool(%superq(debug_work), default=0);
8473      +  %let cleanup_work=%_pipr_bool(%superq(cleanup_work), default=1);
8474      +
8475      +  %_pipe_validate_inputs(data=&data_work, out=&out_work, steps=&steps_work);
8476      +
8477      +  %_pipe_execute(
8478      +    steps=%superq(steps_work),
8479      +    data=&data_work,
8480      +    out=&out_work,
8481      +    validate=&validate_work,
8482      +    use_views=&use_views_work,
8483      +    view_output=&view_output_work,
8484      +    debug=&debug_work,
8485      +    cleanup=&cleanup_work
8486      +  );
8487      +%mend;
